Executive Profile
Alan J. Lacy  Operating Consultant, Oak Hill Capital PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 19 Board Members in 19 different organizations across 26 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. Alan J. Lacy has been Operating Consultant at Oak Hill Capital Partners since 2007. Mr. Lacy served as Chief Executive Officer and President at Sears, Roebuck and Co. since October 2000. Mr. Lacy served as the Chief Executive Officer of Sears Home Improvement Products, Inc. He was In-charge of Lands' End apparel division, the Orchard Supply hardware chain and home and financial services of Sears Holdings Corp. He served as a Senior Advisor of Oak Hill Capital Partners ... since 2007 until 2014. Mr. Lacy served as Incharge of Lands' End apparel division at Sears Holdings Corporation since March 2005. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Sears Holdings Corporation from October 2000 to September 30, 2005. Mr. Lacy served as the Chief Executive Officer of Sears Home Services Group. He served as the Executive Chairman of Sears, Roebuck and Co. since December 2000. He served as an Executive Director of Sears, Roebuck and Co. since 2000. He served as President of Services at Sears, Roebuck and Co. from 1999 to October 2000 and served as its President of Credit from 1997 to 1999 and Additionally Chief Financial Officer from 1998 to 1999. He was employed in a number of executive level positions at companies including Sears, Kraft, Philip Morris and Minnetonka Corporation. He served as Chairman of Dave & Buster's Inc. since September 2014 until June 2017 and its Lead Independent Director of Dave & Buster's Inc. until June 2017. He served as the Chairman of the Board at Dave & Buster's Entertainment, Inc. since September 2014 and served as its Lead Independent Director until June 08, 2017. He served as the Chairman of Sears Canada Inc. from March 2005 to July 29, 2006. Mr. Lacy served as Vice Chairman and Member of Office of the Chairman of Sears Holdings Corporation from September 2005 to July 29, 2006. He serves as Member of the Advisory Board at Fidelity Management & Research Company. He has been a Director of Dave & Buster's Entertainment, Inc. since June 2010. He serves as Independent Trustee/Trustee of various funds in Fidelity Fund Complex. He serves as Director of Bristol-Myers Squibb Farmacêutica Portuguesa, SA. He serves as an Independent Director at Bristol-Myers Squibb Company. He has been a Director of Western Union Financial Services, Inc. since August 28, 2006. He has been an Independent Director of Bristol-Myers Squibb Company since January 02, 2008. He served as a Director of Dave & Buster's Inc. since June 2010 until June 2017. He served as Member of the Advisory Board of various funds in Fidelity Fund Complex. He served as a Director at The Hillman Companies, Inc. since May 2010 until June 30, 2014. He served as an Independent Director of Sears Canada Inc., from 2000 to July 29, 2006. Mr. Lacy served as a Director of The Western Union Company from August 28, 2006 to 2011. Mr. Lacy serves as Director of the Center for Advanced Study in the Behavioral Sciences, Inc at Stanford University. He is a trustee of the California Chapter of The Nature Conservancy and a member of the Advisory Board of the Big Sur Land Trust. He served as a member of the Business Roundtable, a director and member of the Executive Committee of the National Retail Federation and a director of The Western Union Company. In addition, he serves as a trustee of The Field Museum of Natural History, the Lyric Opera of Chicago, the Chicago Botanic Garden and a trustee and former chairman, of the National Parks Conservation Association. Mr. Lacy graduated from the Georgia Institute of Technology with a BS in Industrial Management and earned an MBA from Emory University.Read Full Background




